# Bitwarden Secrets Manager — required secrets
# Create these in your BWS project. The secret name becomes the environment variable name.
# Set BWS_ACCESS_TOKEN in your shell before running start-jamf.sh or start-intune.sh.

# JAMF Pro (start-jamf.sh)
JAMF_URL              Base URL of your JAMF Pro instance, e.g. https://yourorg.jamfcloud.com
JAMF_CLIENT_ID        OAuth2 client ID — create under JAMF Pro > Settings > API Roles and Clients
JAMF_CLIENT_SECRET    OAuth2 client secret for the above client
JAMF_MCP_AUTH_TOKEN   Bearer token(s) required of MCP clients calling this server (comma-separated to allow rotation). Generate with e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`.

# Microsoft Intune (start-intune.sh)
AZURE_TENANT_ID        Azure AD tenant ID (Graph app-only client credentials for device data — unrelated to the Entra auth secrets below)
AZURE_CLIENT_ID        App registration client ID (needs DeviceManagementManagedDevices.Read.All)
AZURE_CLIENT_SECRET    App registration client secret
INTUNE_MCP_AUTH_TOKEN  Bearer token(s) required of MCP clients calling this server (comma-separated to allow rotation). Generate with e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`.

# Entra ID auth for MCP clients (both jamf-server.ts and intune-server.ts; not secrets, but tracked
# here alongside the rest so both servers' required config lives in one place)
ENTRA_OAUTH_ENABLED        "true" to accept Entra-issued bearer tokens on /mcp in addition to the static token above. Can be set independently per server.
ENTRA_TENANT_ID            Entra tenant GUID. Deliberately separate from AZURE_TENANT_ID above even if the value is the same tenant — different app registration, different purpose, don't couple them.
ENTRA_RESOURCE_APP_ID_URI  Application ID URI of the "Desktop Management MCP" resource app registration, e.g. api://desktop-mgmt-mcp
ENTRA_RESOURCE_APP_ID      GUID app ID of the same resource app. Optional, but needed once any MCP client sends the RFC 8707 `resource` parameter (e.g. OpenCode) — Entra then audiences the token to this GUID instead of the URI above, even on the v2 endpoint.
JAMF_MCP_PUBLIC_URL        jamf-server.ts's externally-visible origin, e.g. https://jamf-mcp.colgate.edu (required only when ENTRA_OAUTH_ENABLED=true)
INTUNE_MCP_PUBLIC_URL      intune-server.ts's externally-visible origin, e.g. https://intune-mcp.colgate.edu (required only when ENTRA_OAUTH_ENABLED=true)
